Particularly as we start to understand
the universe a little bit more, or

00:32:21.170 --> 00:32:24.540
the parameters of the universe,
and we look out.

00:32:24.560 --> 00:32:27.660
You know, I know you've got some wonderful
slides you want to share,

00:32:27.690 --> 00:32:32.160
which I think would be a great
backdrop if you want to share them.

00:32:32.240 --> 00:32:35.810
When I think about the topics
that we're talking about today,

00:32:35.840 --> 00:32:38.780
like - where is reincarnation taking us?

00:32:38.810 --> 00:32:44.040
What is the larger scope
and purpose of rebirth?

00:32:44.360 --> 00:32:45.780
I just collect these pictures

00:32:45.810 --> 00:32:49.960
from the NASA, they send them around
every day, and I collect them,

00:32:50.000 --> 00:32:53.460
and I meditate on these pictures.

00:32:53.490 --> 00:32:56.780
I try to envision the enormous distances

00:32:56.810 --> 00:33:03.120
involved and the millions and billions
of stars that are involved.

00:33:03.200 --> 00:33:07.330
And the life that's burgeoning on

00:33:07.360 --> 00:33:11.420
so many of these planets,
in so many of these systems.

00:33:11.450 --> 00:33:13.200
So that the sheer

00:33:14.080 --> 00:33:15.320
fertility,

00:33:15.800 --> 00:33:21.120
the profligate fertility
of the universe, and the scale

00:33:21.200 --> 00:33:27.360
that the universe is thinking of
in order to create and to manifest

00:33:27.680 --> 00:33:34.880
orders, and orders, and orders
of evolving life on this magnitude.

00:33:36.680 --> 00:33:38.000
And then

00:33:38.120 --> 00:33:40.460
to appreciate that we are part of this.

00:33:40.480 --> 00:33:41.520
This

00:33:41.720 --> 00:33:43.020
has been the great,

00:33:43.050 --> 00:33:48.420
great burden of a one-time-through
metaphysics, the belief that we--

00:33:48.450 --> 00:33:52.320
this genius and beauty that we're
seeing in these pictures,

00:33:53.240 --> 00:33:54.660
if our life is meaningless,

00:33:54.690 --> 00:34:00.180
and if it's all random chance, we don't
get to participate in this greatness.

00:34:00.210 --> 00:34:03.140
But if reincarnation is true,

00:34:03.170 --> 00:34:08.060
and if we are really not limited
by the time that this little body lives,

00:34:08.090 --> 00:34:13.460
and if our mind is going to grow
for countless, countless, countless

00:34:13.490 --> 00:34:15.000
incarnations,

00:34:15.320 --> 00:34:16.400
then

00:34:17.000 --> 00:34:20.040
we become intimately part of

00:34:20.200 --> 00:34:27.960
the generative creativity that we see
around us in these vast, magnificent

00:34:29.320 --> 00:34:30.560
images

00:34:31.360 --> 00:34:32.340
of the universe.

00:34:32.370 --> 00:34:35.960
And this then becomes our
playground, you know,

00:34:36.880 --> 00:34:40.380
without the physical body,
this is surely where we live.

00:34:40.410 --> 00:34:41.650
This is our playground.

00:34:41.680 --> 00:34:47.131
And it could be even within
the physical body, you know,

00:34:47.331 --> 00:34:48.980
at some deep level,

00:34:49.000 --> 00:34:50.141
as a hologram,

00:34:50.341 --> 00:34:55.361
you know. That could be a deep truth
that we come to, you know,

00:34:55.561 --> 00:34:58.880
the 'as above, so below' truth.

00:34:59.000 --> 00:35:00.500
And I know you've experienced some

00:35:00.530 --> 00:35:04.100
of that yourself in your experience, your,
you know, journeys.

00:35:04.130 --> 00:35:05.580
And so have I.

00:35:05.610 --> 00:35:09.120
It's a fundamental truth I hold
at the core of my being, you know,

00:35:10.480 --> 00:35:12.980
and in my teachings, also.

00:35:13.010 --> 00:35:16.100
Like I-- we have this profile
called a Hologenetic profile.

00:35:16.130 --> 00:35:18.200
And I name it that because

00:35:19.120 --> 00:35:24.420
it is a map of the inner
workings of our being.

00:35:24.440 --> 00:35:25.520
But

00:35:27.600 --> 00:35:29.440
it kind of has a fractal

00:35:29.880 --> 00:35:33.720
reality that corresponds way beyond

00:35:34.320 --> 00:35:35.400
this

00:35:35.600 --> 00:35:41.640
micro-organism here, of one body. It
is replicated throughout the cosmos.

00:35:43.080 --> 00:35:45.000
Yeah.
Yeah a lot of the great

00:35:45.240 --> 00:35:51.940
super-alchemical teachings of the Taoists,
for example, have explored this in their

00:35:51.970 --> 00:35:55.459
deep, you know, studies
of-- and meditations.

00:35:55.659 --> 00:35:57.940
Where you go within and you find

00:35:57.970 --> 00:36:01.480
the galaxies and the stars,
and where they exist

00:36:01.520 --> 00:36:05.920
in the glands of the body and how
everything has a correspondence.

00:36:08.640 --> 00:36:11.840
And therefore,
knowing those correspondences

00:36:12.040 --> 00:36:20.126
allows your awareness to travel into that
reality and outside your physical body.

00:36:20.326 --> 00:36:23.920
That's, you know, as many people have,

00:36:24.440 --> 00:36:25.980
well, experienced that in dreams,

00:36:26.010 --> 00:36:31.273
or in astral projection, or deep
meditation, or psychedelic journeying.

00:36:31.473 --> 00:36:35.720
I mean, feel free to share some
of your experiences in that.

00:36:35.800 --> 00:36:36.500
Well,

00:36:36.530 --> 00:36:40.980
I've done that as carefully as I can in my
book 'LSD and the Mind of the Universe'.

00:36:41.010 --> 00:36:44.040
But I think the invitation

00:36:44.120 --> 00:36:46.280
is to appreciate

00:36:47.200 --> 00:36:48.840
-- I mean, look, we only became

00:36:49.000 --> 00:36:54.000
conscious of the mother universe about
5000 years ago. We began to have

00:36:54.560 --> 00:36:58.440
sufficient discipline
to drop beneath the conditioning

00:36:59.000 --> 00:37:02.820
of our individual egoic mind,
and to tap into that stream

00:37:02.850 --> 00:37:06.480
of consciousness that we
share with all life.

00:37:06.640 --> 00:37:10.221
We've been walking upright
for 5.8 million years,

00:37:10.421 --> 00:37:14.680
we've only-- we've been operating
with our larger brain about

00:37:14.720 --> 00:37:17.820
200,000 years.

00:37:17.850 --> 00:37:21.380
Writing came in about 5000 years ago.

00:37:21.410 --> 00:37:24.650
The Upanishadic breakthroughs
came in about

00:37:24.680 --> 00:37:26.640
3000-4000 years ago.

00:37:27.160 --> 00:37:28.690
But these are nothing

00:37:28.720 --> 00:37:33.260
compared to the billions and billions
of years that lie ahead of us.

00:37:33.290 --> 00:37:35.100
We're just waking up.

00:37:35.130 --> 00:37:37.500
We're just waking up to who we are.

00:37:37.530 --> 00:37:40.460
And so, naturally, we kind of

00:37:40.490 --> 00:37:44.690
get confused given the enormity
of what we're going into.

00:37:44.720 --> 00:37:48.900
But I think the meditation exercises
that you're describing in those

00:37:48.930 --> 00:37:52.740
philosophical and spiritual traditions,
which have begun to recognise

00:37:52.770 --> 00:37:57.425
the correspondence between
the above and the below,

00:37:57.625 --> 00:38:03.540
naturally, we begin to enter into
exercises where we intentionally,

00:38:03.570 --> 00:38:06.120
sort of, reinforce

00:38:06.560 --> 00:38:09.500
the hybrid nature of our life. That we are

00:38:09.530 --> 00:38:13.100
a spiritual being,
and we are a physical being.

00:38:13.130 --> 00:38:17.170
We are both pure light,
and we are pure green.

00:38:17.200 --> 00:38:22.690
And there are correspondences
in our body which correspond

00:38:22.720 --> 00:38:24.418
to the realities out there.

00:38:24.618 --> 00:38:28.820
And the more we can internalise
and reinforce them and strengthen them

00:38:28.850 --> 00:38:34.520
in our meditational exercises,
then we become a more conscious

00:38:35.120 --> 00:38:37.130
mixing pot.
A more conscious

00:38:37.160 --> 00:38:42.120
kind of mortar and pestle,
integrating the above and the below.

00:38:43.360 --> 00:38:47.680
And if we keep this up for a few
tens of thousands of years,

00:38:48.640 --> 00:38:50.900
and a few millions of years, I mean I--

00:38:50.920 --> 00:38:54.420
sometimes I tell my students the only
serious question we should be asking

00:38:54.450 --> 00:38:58.600
ourselves is - what do you
want to be in a million years?

00:38:58.760 --> 00:39:02.580
Because you're going to be here
in a million years.

00:39:02.610 --> 00:39:05.300
So let's get down to it.

00:39:05.330 --> 00:39:07.580
What is our deepest heart's desire?

00:39:07.610 --> 00:39:09.130
What can we do?

00:39:09.160 --> 00:39:11.040
The fundamental question.

00:39:13.760 --> 00:39:14.580
I heard, a couple of weeks ago,

00:39:14.610 --> 00:39:20.040
I heard a really interesting talk
by Roger Penrose, you know him?

00:39:21.560 --> 00:39:27.040
Really imaginative,
top-level physicist in the world today.

00:39:27.360 --> 00:39:31.000
And he was saying how--

00:39:31.440 --> 00:39:32.520
because

00:39:32.760 --> 00:39:36.300
there's this notion that the universe,
as it's expanding in physics,

00:39:36.320 --> 00:39:38.380
it's getting further,
and further apart and slowing down.

00:39:38.410 --> 00:39:40.060
It's going to reach steady-state.

00:39:40.090 --> 00:39:45.820
And then we're all going to end up in this
kind of slightly distant, dead, lonely

00:39:45.850 --> 00:39:47.720
kind of stopping point.

00:39:51.480 --> 00:39:54.316
And that wasn't his-- that's
not his intuition.

00:39:54.516 --> 00:39:55.100
Or, at least,

00:39:55.130 --> 00:40:00.040
the way he describes it, is that when
you reach that stopping point,

00:40:00.240 --> 00:40:02.740
it's the same as if you've gone incredibly

00:40:02.770 --> 00:40:06.080
fast. As if everything's
come together again,

00:40:06.520 --> 00:40:09.620
because one end of the spectrum
meets the other end of the spectrum.

00:40:09.650 --> 00:40:12.820
So you wouldn't be able to tell
if things are slowing down.

00:40:12.850 --> 00:40:16.840
It actually might be that they look
like they're speeding up. And,

00:40:17.280 --> 00:40:20.900
anyway, so this is my paraphrasing
what he said.

00:40:20.930 --> 00:40:28.200
But the thing that really blew me away,
from a physicist to say, was that he said

00:40:29.640 --> 00:40:33.280
the way he would understand
it is that the logic

00:40:34.120 --> 00:40:39.200
and the kind of elegance
of the universe would be such that that

00:40:40.920 --> 00:40:47.136
kind of condensing point would then give
birth to another universe, out of itself.

00:40:47.336 --> 00:40:48.880
Like, which seems to be

00:40:49.720 --> 00:40:52.420
the-- an elegant logic that the universe
already does,

00:40:52.450 --> 00:40:57.130
as we started by saying rebirth and then
leads to another birth. And another aeon.

00:40:57.160 --> 00:41:00.260
But then he even went further, and he said

00:41:00.290 --> 00:41:02.300
the background radiation

00:41:02.330 --> 00:41:07.900
that we see with-- through our furthest
telescopes, that can now see, like,

00:41:07.930 --> 00:41:11.020
the very, very beginnings of the universe.

00:41:11.050 --> 00:41:12.740
He said there are certain objects

00:41:12.770 --> 00:41:16.482
that we're seeing in there, and I can't
quite remember what he called them,

00:41:16.682 --> 00:41:19.650
but there are certain shapes
and patterns and things that you're

00:41:19.680 --> 00:41:21.820
seeing, and you see them
over and over again.

00:41:21.840 --> 00:41:22.880
And

00:41:22.920 --> 00:41:24.800
his assumption

00:41:25.080 --> 00:41:30.100
was that those were the leftovers
from the previous aeon,

00:41:30.130 --> 00:41:33.600
from the previous universe
that we're seeing,

00:41:34.120 --> 00:41:35.540
and that really blew me away.

00:41:35.570 --> 00:41:37.120
I was like, 'Wow,

00:41:37.240 --> 00:41:39.320
that's from a physicist!'

00:41:39.600 --> 00:41:43.580
Who's willing to
kind of-- who's kind of reached the top

00:41:43.610 --> 00:41:47.160
of his game, he's able
to kind of take a few leaps.

00:41:47.800 --> 00:41:51.560
But that really seemed
to me to be [inaudible].

00:41:52.800 --> 00:41:56.060
I've heard Ervin László describe

00:41:56.090 --> 00:41:59.980
the-- once you reflect
on the extraordinary precision

00:42:00.010 --> 00:42:04.060
of the unfolding of our
universe in the Big Bang,

00:42:04.090 --> 00:42:10.170
the magnitude of the perfection
of the balance of elements that had to be

00:42:10.200 --> 00:42:15.760
present in the first picoseconds
for it to unfold as it has,

00:42:15.960 --> 00:42:17.000
then

00:42:17.560 --> 00:42:18.944
his hypothesis was,

00:42:19.144 --> 00:42:24.480
'Well, do we think that this is the
first time the universe has tried this?'

00:42:24.960 --> 00:42:27.340
There have been expansions
and contractions,

00:42:27.370 --> 00:42:30.820
and expansions and contractions,
and the universe is learning.

00:42:30.840 --> 00:42:31.880
And

00:42:32.400 --> 00:42:35.540
perhaps this isn't the first Big Bang.

00:42:35.570 --> 00:42:38.900
Perhaps this is the 1000th Big Bang.

00:42:38.930 --> 00:42:43.280
And it's gotten-- it's learned
from its previous experiences,

00:42:43.480 --> 00:42:48.130
and that's that background radiation,
the traces of which are there.

00:42:48.160 --> 00:42:50.780
It's constantly ironing out flaws, and

00:42:50.810 --> 00:42:53.540
perfecting, and perfecting,
and perfecting itself.

00:42:53.560 --> 00:42:54.600
Yeah.

00:42:55.560 --> 00:42:56.720
Of course

00:42:57.720 --> 00:42:58.780
this wide view.

00:42:58.810 --> 00:43:00.860
I think it's rich to take the wide view,

00:43:00.890 --> 00:43:05.420
to take the deep view,
and to look at very special developed

00:43:05.450 --> 00:43:10.340
beings who are kind of pushing the edge
of this large view.

00:43:10.370 --> 00:43:13.650
But I want to bring it back down to -

00:43:13.680 --> 00:43:16.940
Okay, how does this
impact me, here, today?

00:43:16.970 --> 00:43:20.780
How does this help me live
with the immediate problems

00:43:20.810 --> 00:43:26.540
that I'm dealing with, or with the
immediate choices that I'm living with?

00:43:26.570 --> 00:43:32.840
And I think it does, in the sense that
by-- it's an invitation

00:43:33.040 --> 00:43:39.620
to look at our life
as an intentional, intelligent

00:43:39.650 --> 00:43:46.160
convocation of circumstances,
not as a meaningless and not as a

00:43:46.760 --> 00:43:50.700
blind, deterministic
combination of circumstances.

00:43:50.730 --> 00:43:55.770
And if we engage our life circumstances as a--

00:43:55.970 --> 00:43:58.400
an intentional challenge

00:43:58.520 --> 00:44:01.495
chosen us-- chosen for us, by us,

00:44:01.695 --> 00:44:04.020
at a time when we knew more,

00:44:04.050 --> 00:44:09.300
and we start to make choices in terms
of-- out of a deeper sense of engagement.

00:44:09.330 --> 00:44:11.340
That our choice does matter.

00:44:11.370 --> 00:44:14.100
Even if we don't see how it changes

00:44:14.130 --> 00:44:19.580
things immediately, we can trust that it
does change things in the long term.

00:44:19.600 --> 00:44:21.000
Then I think

00:44:21.520 --> 00:44:26.300
we will find that life changes,
the circumstances of our life changes.

00:44:26.330 --> 00:44:31.440
Things that were hard become soft,
things that were barren becomes richer.

00:44:31.840 --> 00:44:35.940
That's your experience
I'm sure with Gene Keys.

00:44:35.960 --> 00:44:37.560
Yeah.
And it gives

00:44:37.720 --> 00:44:39.560
us like-- for me, it gives us

00:44:40.880 --> 00:44:43.100
like a different kind of backdrop

00:44:43.130 --> 00:44:47.780
with which to
tackle the problems of the world.

00:44:47.810 --> 00:44:54.040
So the problems that we see today
around us, that worry us so much,

00:44:54.520 --> 00:44:59.180
it gives us an empowered view
from a much wider view.

00:44:59.200 --> 00:44:59.700
Like, to look at what we've just been

00:44:59.730 --> 00:45:02.780
looking at, those
cosmic background images.

00:45:02.800 --> 00:45:04.580
And then you come to the world today

00:45:04.610 --> 00:45:09.160
and you look at this tiny little
blue planet, with its problems,

00:45:09.560 --> 00:45:11.280
and, you know-- and they're very real

00:45:12.160 --> 00:45:13.980
and they're causing
a great deal of suffering.

00:45:14.010 --> 00:45:15.260
They always have done.

00:45:15.280 --> 00:45:16.320
But

00:45:16.840 --> 00:45:20.000
they're now more easily
seen than ever before.

00:45:20.120 --> 00:45:23.480
And we've enacted them globally
because of our technology.

00:45:23.800 --> 00:45:24.840
So

00:45:26.000 --> 00:45:28.380
we are, you know-- it means that, for me,

00:45:28.410 --> 00:45:34.460
I'm constantly reminding people that,
you know, action that comes

00:45:34.490 --> 00:45:41.200
from a state of trust is very different
from action that comes from fear.

00:45:41.600 --> 00:45:44.210
If we can dive into that field of wider

00:45:44.240 --> 00:45:48.060
trust, and we begin to make friends
with our own death. You know,

00:45:48.090 --> 00:45:54.140
instead of being-- it being something
that's kind of like, 'Ugh, it's coming.

00:45:54.170 --> 00:45:55.920
You know, I'm running out of time.'

00:45:55.960 --> 00:46:00.900
Instead of, like, that view, and having
this long-term view as an individual.

00:46:00.930 --> 00:46:04.140
And even, like, what I'm doing

00:46:04.160 --> 00:46:05.600
as a community,

00:46:06.680 --> 00:46:10.940
how about if a whole community
of people on the same wavelength

00:46:10.970 --> 00:46:14.210
play with this together? Like,
we're all going to come back,

00:46:14.240 --> 00:46:17.060
you know, we're going to return,
and we're going to return into this same

00:46:17.090 --> 00:46:20.660
-- I mean this is why I've
created these teachings

00:46:20.680 --> 00:46:22.200
-- I haven't created them, they've
appeared,

00:46:22.520 --> 00:46:23.600
because

00:46:23.840 --> 00:46:26.100
we can come back into them.

00:46:26.130 --> 00:46:28.700
And we can begin to, like

00:46:28.720 --> 00:46:30.420
-- and the teachings
are just the teachings.

00:46:30.450 --> 00:46:35.180
They're just enable us to kind-- to give
a focal point so that we can do our work,

00:46:35.210 --> 00:46:41.210
our continuous, progressive
evolutionary work as communities,

00:46:41.240 --> 00:46:45.020
rather than like, 'Okay, you've done
this great work, and then you've gone.

00:46:45.050 --> 00:46:48.055
And yeah, I might be reborn, but where?'

00:46:48.255 --> 00:46:54.140
If you're born into the same community
of beings, of souls, who are all committed

00:46:54.170 --> 00:47:00.140
to transmuting karma of the planet,
and come in with different gifts, and

00:47:00.170 --> 00:47:03.866
genius, and skills,
in different locations around the world,

00:47:04.066 --> 00:47:07.380
but we're interconnected
through the Internet, and through

00:47:07.410 --> 00:47:11.820
our body of teachings that kind of
have a resonance in our soul.

00:47:11.850 --> 00:47:15.660
So we recognise them again,
even as a child.

00:47:15.690 --> 00:47:20.720
You know, and synchronicity
helps us to find them. Suddenly,

00:47:20.960 --> 00:47:23.340
it's a different playground again!

00:47:23.370 --> 00:47:28.080
You don't have to say goodbye
to all your loved ones forever.

00:47:29.240 --> 00:47:31.500
You're going to remember them in different

00:47:31.530 --> 00:47:34.580
way-- you're going to bring
more of that awareness

00:47:34.610 --> 00:47:38.100
down through the transitionary
